I really wanted to like this place.  First, the food is wayyyy tooo salty.  I used to live in Brooklyn and missed the delicious cheese pies I used to get from a place on 5th Avenue. I was driving through and saw this place hoping they would be just as good. Unfortunately not only was the food bad but they are dishonest as well.  I ordered cheese pies and a combination pie and some spinach triangles. When I got home I saw they forgot to put in one of the cheese pies. When I called and spoke to Ahmed he said he would credit me after offering me to come it up. I explained that I lived too far to come back. The conversation left off that he would credit me.  4 days later he still has not credited me. I called to see why and he insists that crediting me would be difficult.  He offered to give me cash back. To drive all the way back to Brooklyn for something that should be so easy and what gas and time would cost me, is not worth it.  Disappointed with the service to say the least.  In addition later that evening I get a call from the fraud department on the card I used. This was the only place I used my card in, in months.  When I handed my card to pay it disappeared somewhere in the back and who knows whether someone working their swiped my numbers. Coincidence could be, but this just added to the bad taste their food added to my mouth. Never again.

Over the last 3 years I developed a love / hate relationship with Karam. Sometimes their food is so good, and sometimes I question why on earth I decided to get food from them. There is definitely an issue with consistency.  Tonight I placed an order with them, and I'd have to say that I've finally had it. I ordered the garlic sauce which has always been either "spot-on" or too pungent. Tonight it was so severely pungent that I couldn't eat it. It was like chewing a whole head of garlic. Sometimes I just power through a bit of it and let the rest sit in the fridge for a few days to calm it down, but today's case was beyond anything I'd had from them previously.  Also, I was in the mood for some French fries, so I ordered some. They're usually pretty crispy, hot, and tasty. Today they tasted old, cold, and like they'd been refried and left to sit before making it into my order.  ...Karam, we had a good run, I don't think I'm coming back. I'll just have to find another authentic Lebanese spot.

Avid middle eastern food lover, hard to find truly ethnic tasting food in the 5 boroughs. We try to order from this place at least once a month and the food is always incredible. I'm Lebanese and we've tried many different Middle Eastern restaurants over the years and we just keep coming back to Karam. We usually get the Beef Shish Kabab platter with rice, hummus/babaghanoush and grape leaves, Lahmajeen pie, Tabouleh, Yogurt Salad, Pita, and a couple of Kibbeh balls.
